      <prefercite id="aspace_1cadd5e4fb3dd7b5bddf6918b71387fe">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Maurice Emile Henri Rotival Papers (MS 1380). Manuscripts and Archives. Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_9005b69f4a0bc40b33082cae49102542">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Maurice Emile Henri Rotival, born in 1892, was one of the founders of city and regional planning. He was a graduate of L'Ecole Central in Paris. He developed major renewal plans for Algiers, Madagascar, Caracas, Reims, and New Haven, Connecticut. He also founded the faculty for city planning at the Yale University School of Fine Arts and taught at Yale in various capacities in the 1940s and 1950s. He died in Paris in February 1980.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_6dea93100bf0050545cd7cd100e76336">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of reports, drawings, and correspondence, documenting the professional work, particularly city renewal planning, of Maurice Emile Henri Rotival during the years 1944-1963.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
